imary mission is to stimulate and support research in the humanities arts and social sciences especially of an interdisciplinary kind at the university of kansas the center brings together faculty and graduate students with common interests from various disciplines to enable them to build on each others ideas and to share their knowledge within the university and with the wider community the center s collateral mission is to sponsor special programs that engage the university and the wider community in dialogue on issues that bring the humanities to bear on the quality of life for all citizens it creates events on and beyond campus that seek to understand our past present and future our values and identities and the essential issues we face as individuals and communities what s new at the hall center hall family foundation awards to support hall center programs april distinguished professor of american history robin d g kelley to speak on war race and democracy in humanities lecture series april international human rights scholar michael ignatieff to speak on moral progress in humanities lecture series april panel on the american dream to take place on april march midwest association of graduate schools honors hall center s applied humanities initiative with award for excellence and innovation in graduate education march professor and coordinator of anti slavery and human trafficking initiative to speak on human trafficking in the heartland march hall center to host th annual celebration of books march humanities faculty members and graduate students receive hall center travel awards march hall center announces resident fellows february hall center visiting regional humanities faculty program winners announced for february historian explorer and acclaimed professor of history iain mccalman to speak on the great barrier reef in humanities lecture series february hall center program to offer graduate students practical insights on careers in applied humanities and adv